{"TopicId":208553,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Gravity assist helper mod?","CreatedByName":"Rasputin","CreatedById":221780,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-11T18:09:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rasputin","CreatedById":221780,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-11T18:09:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile trying to plan my first gravity assist maneuver in vanilla, I tallied up some features I was wishing I had access to. Today I looked around for mods that might contain them already, before I take the step of rolling my own. Couldn\u0027t find most of them however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any mods that cover the following?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1: Ability to specify a maneuver node in terms of angles and magnitude instead of a Cartesian delta\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2: Ability to visualize position and rotation of solar system bodies at a given future time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3: Locking a maneuver node\u0027s time relative another, so that changing the time of one adjusts the other as well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4: Ability to adjust time of a maneuver forwards or backwards by \u0022synodic\u0022 orbits instead of the default, \u0022sidereal\u0022 orbits - for instance, if currently in orbit of Kerbin, being able to add one orbit plus the angle that the Mun moves in the interim, so that the maneuver has the same argument relative the Mun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rasputin","CreatedById":221780,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-11T20:20:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...I found that Precise Maneuver has something very similar to point 1. Suspect it doesn\u0027t support maintaining that angle if maneuvers are added or changed before it, though, which would be nice too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-12T03:32:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Emaybe Sling Shotter Res